From ed5d939fdd49df5e5b52b247f0154639c923e2dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 21:02:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.8: Error boundaries + global error handlers
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a safety net under the app so runtime failures no longer result
in white-screen crashes. Three coordinated pieces:

1. src/components/ErrorBoundary.jsx (new)
   React class-based error boundary with a branded recoverable fallback
   UI. Catches render-phase errors and offers 'Try again' + 'Go home'
   recovery actions. Includes a collapsible 'Technical details' section
   for debugging without alarming non-technical users.

2. src/lib/query-client.js (upgraded)
   QueryClient now has queryCache.onError and mutationCache.onError
   handlers. Query errors on BACKGROUND refresh (not initial load)
   surface as toasts; all errors log to console. Mutation errors log
   only — existing call sites already handle their own mutation
   failures with try/catch + toast.error, so this is log-only to avoid
   duplicate toasts. The comment in query-client.js notes that T2.2
   will centralize those when it migrates to useMutation.

3. src/main.jsx (updated)
   window.addEventListener('unhandledrejection') logs stray promise
   rejections that escape try/catch + react-query handling. This is
   the observability hook point for future Sentry/LogRocket work.

4. src/App.jsx
   Wraps <AuthenticatedApp /> in <ErrorBoundary>. Placement is
   inside Router (so Link/useNavigate work in the fallback if needed)
   but outside AuthenticatedApp (so auth-related crashes still get
   caught).

What it does NOT catch (by React design, documented in the hook):
- Errors in event handlers — use try/catch + toast.error locally
- Errors in async code — use useQuery/useMutation or the global listener
- SSR errors — not applicable, Vite client-only

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors, 0 warnings on touched files
- npm run build: succeeds
- Bundle size impact: +~2KB gzipped (one class component + 3 icons)
